-- Nigeria's Access Bank targets 20 pct loan growth in 2014
-- By Chijioke Ohuocha
-- Wed Aug 27, 2014 09:12AM EDT
-- None



LAGOS, Aug 27 (Reuters) - Nigeria's Access Bank <ACCESS.LG> expects loan growth of 20 percent in 2014, after a 17 percent increase in the first half, its chief executive said on Wednesday.

Access Bank's loan book stood at 811 billion naira ($5 billion) in 2013, CEO Herbert Wigwe, told a conference call presenting its half-year results.